message.content:
A 'Quercus ilex' is an evergreen tree found in the Mediterranean region.
Its leaves are leathery and dark green, with a shiny, waxy surface.
The bark is rough and grey-brown, with deep grooves and fissures.
The tree can grow up to 25 meters tall and has a wide, rounded crown.
It produces small acorns that are a source of food for birds and wildlife.
'Quercus ilex' is commonly used in landscaping due to its attractive appearance.
It can be found in parks, gardens, and wooded areas throughout the Mediterranean.
